<section class="hero" style="background-color: var(--color-primary); color: var(--color-white);">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="hero-title" style="color: var(--color-white);">Flat Design Principles</h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle" style="color: var(--color-white);">
      The foundational concepts that define Flat Design's bold, two-dimensional aesthetic.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="background-color: var(--color-turquoise);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="principle-card mb-lg" style="background-color: var(--color-primary); color: var(--color-white);">
      <svg class="icon icon-lg icon-white" viewBox="0 0 48 48" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <rect x="12" y="12" width="24" height="24"/>
        <path d="M18 12V6H42V30H36"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="principle-number" style="color: var(--color-white);">01</div>
      <h2 class="principle-title" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--color-white);">Completely Flat - No Depth Effects</h2>
      <div class="principle-description" style="color: var(--color-white);">
        <p>
          The defining principle: absolutely no shadows, gradients, bevels, or any effect that suggests depth. 
          Pure two-dimensional design that embraces the digital medium rather than trying to mimic physical materials.
        </p>
        <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-md); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-white);">
          Key Characteristics:
        </h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Zero shadows:</strong> Not even subtle drop shadows</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>No gradients:</strong> Solid colors only</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Flat buttons:</strong> Simple rectangles with color changes on hover</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>2D icons:</strong> Simple outlines or solid shapes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="principle-card mb-lg" style="background-color: var(--color-success); color: var(--color-white);">
      <svg class="icon icon-lg icon-white" viewBox="0 0 48 48" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <circle cx="24" cy="24" r="16"/>
        <circle cx="18" cy="18" r="2" fill="white"/>
        <circle cx="30" cy="18" r="2" fill="white"/>
        <circle cx="18" cy="30" r="2" fill="white"/>
        <circle cx="30" cy="30" r="2" fill="white"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="principle-number" style="color: var(--color-white);">02</div>
      <h2 class="principle-title" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--color-white);">Bright, Vibrant Colors</h2>
      <div class="principle-description" style="color: var(--color-white);">
        <p>
          Flat Design uses bold, saturated colors to create visual interest without depth. The famous 
          "Flat UI Colors" palette became iconic - bright blues, greens, oranges, and reds that pop on screen.
        </p>
        <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-md); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-white);">
          Color Principles:
        </h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>High saturation:</strong> Vivid, pure colors</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Color blocking:</strong> Large areas of solid color</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Clear hierarchy:</strong> Different colors for different elements</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Flat UI palette:</strong> #3498DB, #2ECC71, #F39C12, #E74C3C</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="principle-card mb-lg" style="background-color: var(--color-warning); color: var(--color-white);">
      <svg class="icon icon-lg icon-white" viewBox="0 0 48 48" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <path d="M12 12H36M24 12V40M18 40H30"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="principle-number" style="color: var(--color-white);">03</div>
      <h2 class="principle-title" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--color-white);">Simple, Clean Typography</h2>
      <div class="principle-description" style="color: var(--color-white);">
        <p>
          Sans-serif fonts with clear hierarchies and bold weights. Typography becomes a major design 
          element when you remove textures and depth. Open Sans, Lato, and system fonts are common choices.
        </p>
        <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-md); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-white);">
          Typographic Elements:
        </h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Sans-serif only:</strong> Clean, modern typefaces</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Bold headings:</strong> 700-800 font weights</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Clear hierarchy:</strong> Size and weight create structure</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Ample spacing:</strong> Generous line height and margins</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="principle-card mb-lg" style="background-color: var(--color-danger); color: var(--color-white);">
      <svg class="icon icon-lg icon-white" viewBox="0 0 48 48" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <rect x="8" y="8" width="32" height="32" rx="4"/>
        <line x1="16" y1="24" x2="32" y2="24"/>
        <line x1="24" y1="16" x2="24" y2="32"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="principle-number" style="color: var(--color-white);">04</div>
      <h2 class="principle-title" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--color-white);">Minimal Interface Elements</h2>
      <div class="principle-description" style="color: var(--color-white);">
        <p>
          Strip interfaces down to essential elements. Simple geometric shapes - rectangles, circles. 
          Line icons with 2px strokes. Focus on content and functionality rather than decoration.
        </p>
        <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-md); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-white);">
          UI Approach:
        </h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Simple shapes:</strong> Rectangles with 4px border-radius</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Line icons:</strong> Outline style, 2px stroke weight</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Minimal chrome:</strong> Reduce interface elements</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Content focus:</strong> Let content be the star</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <div class="principle-card mb-lg" style="background-color: var(--color-info); color: var(--color-white);">
      <svg class="icon icon-lg icon-white" viewBox="0 0 48 48" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <path d="M12 24L20 32L36 16"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="principle-number" style="color: var(--color-white);">05</div>
      <h2 class="principle-title" style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--color-white);">Digital Honesty</h2>
      <div class="principle-description" style="color: var(--color-white);">
        <p>
          Embrace the digital medium. Don't pretend buttons are physical objects. Digital interfaces 
          should look digital, not try to mimic leather, wood, or paper. Honest representation of the medium.
        </p>
        <h3 style="margin-top: var(--space-md); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-white);">
          Philosophy:
        </h3>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>No skeuomorphism:</strong> No fake textures</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Digital-first:</strong> Design for screens, not paper</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Authentic materials:</strong> Pixels are the material</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);"><strong>Function over metaphor:</strong> Direct communication</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="background-color: var(--color-neutral);">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title mb-lg">Additional Core Concepts</h2>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Responsive by Nature</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          Flat elements scale perfectly across devices. Simple shapes and colors work at any 
          resolution. No texture files to resize. Ideal for the mobile-first era.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-success);">Performance Focus</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          Flat designs load faster. No heavy texture images. Simple CSS creates buttons. 
          SVG icons scale infinitely. Better performance on all devices.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-warning);">Grid-Based Layouts</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          Clean grids organize flat interfaces. Tile-based layouts like Windows Metro. 
          Card-based designs. Structured without visible borders.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3 class="card-title" style="color: var(--color-danger);">Color as Interface</h3>
        <p class="card-content">
          With no depth cues, color becomes the primary differentiator. Different colors 
          mean different things. Color states replace shadow states.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

